article:
The '[[Roman Catholic (term)|Roman]] [[Catholic Church]]' in its entirety
contains more than 3,000 ecclesiastical jurisdictions, including over 600
archdioceses as well as military ordinariates, apostolic administrations,
apostolic prefectures, apostolic vicariates, territorial and personal
prelatures, and missions sui juris around the world.

This is a structural list to show the relationships of each diocese to one
another, grouped by ecclesiastical province, within each episcopal conference,
within each continent or other geographical area.

The list is incomplete, but as articles are written up, more will be added.

:For an alphabetical list, see: [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses
(alphabetical)]]
headings: Directly subject to the Holy See
